<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Perlohmanniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">PERLOHMANNIIDAE</taxonomicName>
Grandjean, 1954
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Berlese (1916a) reckoned 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Perlohmaniidae" genus="Perlohmannia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Perlohmannia</taxonomicName>
among the representatives of the tribe 
<taxonomicName pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="tribe" tribe="Lohmannini">Lohmannini</taxonomicName>
, but Grandjean (1931) separated the genus from this tribe and thought that it were possible to include it in a new tribe 
<taxonomicName pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="tribe" tribe="Trhypochthonini">Trhypochthonini</taxonomicName>
. This opinion has been corrected by him in 1954 when the family 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Perlohmanniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Perlohmanniidae</taxonomicName>
was created, and in 1958 when the family was placed in a superfamily 
<taxonomicName pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Perlohmannoidea">Perlohmannoidea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Collohmanniidae" genus="Collohmannia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Collohmannia</taxonomicName>
Sellnick (1922) certainly does not belong to the 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Perlohmanniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Perlohmanniidae</taxonomicName>
, so that for the moment the family consists of only one genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
